for iii in range(3):#
    score_name = "score" + str(iii)
    score_name = []
    for n in range(1, 9):
        for jjj in data[1:]:
            score_name.append(int(jjj[3+iii])) ##
    gk = 0;jg = 0;lh = 0;bc = 0;yx = 0#0
    for i in score_name:#
        if i < 60:
            gk += 1
        elif i>= 60 and i < 70:
            jg += 1
        elif i>= 70 and i < 80:
            lh += 1
        elif i>= 80 and i < 90:
            bc += 1
        elif i>= 90 and i <= 100:
            yx += 1
    x = ["0-59", "60-69", "70-79", "80-89", "90-100"] #
    y = [gk,jg,lh,bc,yx]#
    color = ['r','y','b']  #
    plt.bar(x, y, alpha=1, color = color[iii],bottom = np.array([iii]))#1   
plt.title("",fontproperties = 'SimHei',fontsize = 20) #
plt.ylabel("",fontproperties = 'SimHei',fontsize = 20)
plt.xlabel("",fontproperties = 'SimHei',fontsize = 20)
plt.show()
